column1: [0]:the world economic forum predicts automation will displace 75 million jobs by 2025 but create 133 million new ones.
[1]:heavy social media use is linked to increased anxiety and depression, especially due to social comparison.
[2]:ai can improve healthcare, but concerns about data privacy persist.
[3]:ai systems can reflect biases, leading to inequality, especially in hiring.
[4]:the un stresses the need for global standards on privacy, cybersecurity, and ai ethics.
